ter told Fox News. "}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Officials are looking at sending 800 troops, but one official called that estimate &#x201C;the floor&#x201D; &#x2013; saying it could increase as military planners work through the request from DHS to help the Border Patrol. "}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"The formal approval comes after President Trump announced earlier he&#x2019;s &quot;bringing out the military&quot; to address what he&apos;s calling a national emergency at the border. Thousands of Central American migrants are now making their way through Mexico in hopes of reaching the United States."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"The additional troops are to provide what one official described as logistical support to the Border Patrol. The support troops would include engineers, as well as medical and aviation support units."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"The Pentagon said in a statement: &quot;The DoD will provide Defense Support of Civil Authorities with planning assistance, engineering support (temporary barriers, barricades, and fencing), fixed and rotary wing aviation support to move CBP personnel, medical teams to triage, treat and prepare for commercial transport of patients, command and control facilities, temporary housing for CBP personnel, and personal protective equipment for CBP personnel.&quot;"}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Combat troops are not being considered, but the bulk of the reinforcements going to the border are active-duty forces."}},{"is":"video-inline","props":{"type":"video","title":"Who is General James Mattis?","caption":"'No Better Friend, No Worse Enemy' author Jim Proser shares insight about the life and distinguished career of General James Mattis.","videoId":"5820837493001","imageUrl":"https:\u002F\u002Fmedia2.foxnews.com\u002FBrightCove\u002F694940094001\u002F2018\u002F08\u002F11\u002F694940094001_5820834502001_5820837493001-vs.jpg","originalImageUrl":"https:\u002F\u002Fmedia2.foxnews.com\